[[Image:javapolis1.jpg|200px|thumb|JavaPolis 2006]]
[[Image:javapolis2.jpg|200px|thumb|Cinema screens]]

'''AgileNCR''', an annual [[Agile software development]] conference organized by [[Xebia]] and Agile enthusiasts of the NCR region. It takes place every year around April. Anurag Shrivastava started NCR Agile User Group which was later transformed into Agile NCR Conference. The first conference was in 2006, and in 2009 there were 35 organisations participating. Every year there is a new theme to the conference and presentations range from beginner to expert level adopters of Agile.

==Location==

AgileNCR takes place in the [[National Capital Region (India)|National Capital Region (NCR)]] of India. The conference is usually hosted in an [[educational institute]] or in a [[conference room]] at a hotel. As a result, the speaker video and slides are projected on screens.

